# Design system migration rules

- Never modify anything inside apps/web/src/design-system/
- Never change backend code, API calls, Prisma schema, or auth logic
- Never change the existing PageHeader component (props: eyebrow, titleId, description — different API from design-system's PageHeader)
- Never change App.tsx routing logic (hash-based routing)
- Never replace the existing AppLayout/sidebar/navigation shell with design-system's AppShell/Sidebar/Topbar — only swap leaf-level UI primitives (Button, Table, Input, Badge, Card, Modal, Alert, Spinner) inside existing pages
- Never install new npm packages or modify package.json
- Never read, print, or modify .env, .env.local, or any credential file
- Never rewrite copy, labels, or text content while swapping components — preserve exact existing strings unless the new component's own status mapping replaces redundant inline text (e.g. StatusBadge's built-in label)
- Never reformat untouched code, reorder unrelated imports, or run a project-wide formatter/linter --fix during this task — keep diffs scoped to the actual component swap
- Never git push, open a PR, or run destructive git commands (reset --hard, force push, branch deletion) without explicit confirmation from the user first
- Commit after every single file using `git add <specific file path>` — never `git add .` or `git add -A` during this task
- If a build/typecheck error can't be fixed in 2 attempts, stop and report the exact error instead of guessing further

## Long status reports
- Whenever a status report, diagnosis, or summary would exceed roughly 30 lines, write the full report to a file instead of printing it entirely in chat.
- File location: repo root, named _status_report.md (leading underscore signals scratch file, never part of source).
- In chat, print only: confirmation the file was written, its path, and a 2-3 sentence summary of the headline finding.
- Never include this scratch file in any git add or commit — if asked to commit, explicitly exclude it.
- This applies to any future block, not just this one.
